.co.uk/finance-finder\" title=\"Business finance in your area\" rel=\"external\">Business Finance for You</a> website.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Selling shares</h2>\n\n<p>If you’re thinking of bringing in new investors, they&rsquo;ll want to know how much your business could increase in value if they buy shares. To work this out, they&rsquo;ll need to know how much their investment will increase your sales and profitability.</p>\n\n<p>You&rsquo;ll need to provide potential lenders and investors with a financial model showing:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>how your business will spend the extra money to increase sales and profitability</li>\n  <li>how initial costs and increased ongoing costs will affect your cash flow</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Increases in sales usually only happen after taking on additional costs like employing more staff, moving to larger premises or putting in bigger orders for raw materials. You&rsquo;ll need to take all of these into account in your financial planning.</p>\n\n"}]},"updated_at":"2012-10-22T15:26:33+00:00","tags":[{"title":"Setting up","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/business%2Fsetting-up.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes Self Assessment, self-employment and starting a business","type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=business%2Fsetting-up","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/business/setting-up"},"parent":{"title":"Businesses and self-employed","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/business.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Information about starting up and running a business in the UK, including help if you're self employed or a sole trader.","type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=business","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/business"},"parent":null}},{"title":"Business Link","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/businesslink.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":null,"type":"legacy_source"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https:/