ed-company\" title=\"prepare annual accounts\">statutory accounts</a> - to <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> within 12 months of the end of the company&rsquo;s year end.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n\n<h2>Telling <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> the company has started business</h2>\n\n<p>If the company hasn&rsquo;t traded before, <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://online.hmrc.gov.uk/registration/newbusiness\" title=\"Register a new business for tax with HMRC\">register it with <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr>.</a></p>\n\n<p>If the company was trading but then stopped and later resumed trading, fill in form CT204 and send it to your company&rsquo;s <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://search2.hmrc.gov.uk/kbroker/hmrc/locator/locator.jsp?type=0\" title=\"Find a Corporation Tax office\">Corporation Tax office.</a></p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/ctsa/forms/ct204active.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Form CT204' (PDF, 71KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download &lsquo;Form CT204&rsquo; (PDF, 71KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/ctsa/forms/ct204notes.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Notes for form CT204' (PDF, 51KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download &lsquo;Notes for form CT204&rsquo; (PDF, 51KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Deadlines for accounts and returns</h2>\n\n<p>While your company was dormant, you will still have been sending accounts to Companies House each year - so your Companies House reporting dates will stay the same for annual returns and accounts. </p>\n\n<p>But your company&rsquo;s Corporation Tax accounting period will begin when the company starts business activities.</p>\n\n<p>You can:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>keep the company&rsquo;s accounting reference date the same with Companies House</li>\n  <li>create <a href=\"/prepare-file-annual-accounts-for-limited-company/prepare-annual-accounts\" title=\"Prepare annual accounts\">statutory accounts</a> as usual for the 12 months up until the accounting reference date</li>\n  <li>send these accounts to Companies House and use them to complete your Company Tax Return</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>If you take these steps, your Companies House accounting reference date and the end of your Corporation Tax accounting period will be the same.</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"example\">\n<p><strong>Example</strong> </p>\n\n<p>Your non-trading or dormant company&rsquo;s accounting reference date is 30 September. It starts business activities again on 1 May.</p>\n\n<p>Make a set of statutory accounts for the usual period from 1 October to 30 September.</p>\n\n<p>Send your accounts to Companies House and your Company Tax Return for the period 1 May to 30 September to <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr>.</p>\n\n<p>After this, you&rsquo;ll need to complete accounts and Company Tax Returns from 1 October to 30 September each year.</p>\n</div>\n\n"},"updated_at":"2012-10-22T15:26:29+00:00","tags":[{"title":"Running a limited company","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/business%2Flimited-company.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes registering, setting up, company accounts and tax returns","type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=business%2Flimited-company","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/business/limited-company"},"parent":{"title":"Businesses and self-employed","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/business.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Information about starting up and running a business in the UK, including help if you're self employed or a sole trader.","type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=business","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/business"},"parent":null}},{"title":"Setting up","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/business%2Fsetting-up.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes Self Assessmen